03/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- The government allocated the 2011 budget for religious communities on Wednesday (March 2nd) following a proposal from the ministry of tourism, culture, youth and sports.
The special fund, amounting to over 700,000 euros, will mainly go to the Muslim community, the Orthodox Church, the Catholic Church, and the Bektashi community.
Most of the money will be used for salaries and the reconstruction of religious buildings.
(Shekulli, Balkan Web, Telegrafi - 02/03/11)
